President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Carl Shapiro as a member of the Council of Economic Advisors. Shapiro is currently the Deputy Assistant Attorney General for Economics at the Antitrust Division of the United States Department of Justice. He is also a professor at the University of California at Berkeley. If confirmed, Shapiro will replace Cecilia Rouse, who is leaving the Council to return to Princeton University. Shapiro has extensive experience in antitrust economics and is the co-author of the book "Information Rules: A Strategic Guide to the Network Economy." He earned his Ph.D. in Economics from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology in 1981. President Obama expressed gratitude for Shapiro's knowledge and dedication and looks forward to working with him in the future.